  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2020-04-21",
    "date": "2020-04-28T17:34:37Z",
    "text": "Equal Access to COVID-19 Relief Act\n\nThis bill expands access to specified assistance related to COVID-19 (i.e., coronavirus disease 2019) by providing that the receipt of legal gaming revenue shall not disqualify a person from receiving certain benefits.\n\nUnder current law, businesses that derive more than one-third of their gross annual revenue from legal gaming activities are ineligible for Small Business Administration loans."
  },
